# Lumiverb — Algorithm Reference

These algorithms are extracted from the proven PoC. Do not deviate from them without
explicit approval. Read the full reference doc before writing any implementation.

## Video Scene Segmentation → @docs/reference/video_scene_segmentation.md
Key constants — do not change:
- `PHASH_THRESHOLD = 51` bits (Hamming distance trigger)
- `TEMPORAL_CEILING_SEC = 30.0` (max scene length)
- `DEBOUNCE_SEC = 3.0` (minimum time between phash-triggered cuts)
- `SKIP_FRAMES_BEST = 2` (skip first 2 frames per scene for sharpness selection)
- `OUT_WIDTH = 480` (FFmpeg pipe width for scene detection pass)
- `PTS_QUEUE_TIMEOUT = 10.0` (SyncError if FFmpeg hangs)

## Worker Base & Lease → @docs/reference/worker_base_pattern.md
Key constants — do not change:
- Lease duration: 10 minutes
- Heartbeat interval: 15s
- Stale worker threshold: 60s
- Idle poll: max 5s

## BM25 Similarity Search → @docs/reference/bm25_similarity_search.md
Key constants — do not change:
- `similarity_min_score = 0.65`
- `similarity_floor = 0.35`
- `similarity_step = 0.10`
- `similarity_min_results = 3`
- Tags appear **twice** in query tokens (BM25 weight boost — do not remove)
- Score filtering is client-side after HTTP response (Quickwit query-level score syntax not stable)
- Multi-index routing: one index per AI model version, fetched per request (no cache)

## AI Vision & Metadata → @docs/reference/ai_vision_metadata.md
Key constants — do not change:
- `SHARPNESS_MAX_VARIANCE = 1000.0`
- `MOONDREAM_TIMEOUT = 120s`
- Face detection confidence: `0.5`
- Semantic dedup threshold: `85%` (rapidfuzz token ratio)
- Three Moondream calls per image: caption → tags → OCR
- Tags: order-preserving dedup, comma-separated answer parsing
- OCR: store `null` if response is literally `"None"`
- EXIF: strip all keys starting with `MakerNote` before storing
